main event: A group of witnesses reported seeing an unidentified object in the sky over Normal, Illinois, on March 22, 1966.
interesting points: Witnesses described the object as having red, white, and green blinking lights,Several people called to report seeing a UFO, but it was later concluded to be a DC-3 airplane,The DC-3 was operating unusually low over the city before landing at Bloomington airport,The sky was overcast, which made it difficult to gauge the object's size, and the wind conditions might have influenced the lack of sound during the sighting,The investigation suggested that the lighting configuration of the DC-3 matched the descriptions given by witnesses of the UFO.
witness description: Civilian witnesses, including young children and adults playing outside
